-- Gonzaga Eyes No. 1 NCAA Tournament Seed After Winning WCC Title
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2013-03-12T04:52:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-12/gonzaga-eyes-no-1-ncaa-tournament-seed-after-winning-wcc-title.html
Gonzaga University probably locked
up a No. 1 seed in the National Collegiate Athletic Association
men’s basketball tournament by beating Saint Mary’s 65-51 in the
West Coast Conference title game  Davidson College,  James Madison  University, Western
Kentucky University and Iona College also earned automatic NCAA
bids by winning conference tournaments yesterday. Ten of the 31
automatic bids have now been awarded, while another 37 schools
will receive at-large invitations.  Gonzaga, headed to the NCAA tournament for the 15th
straight season, won its 11th WCC title a week after becoming
the No. 1 team in the national polls. Kelly Olynyk had 21 points
and 12 rebounds last night in  Las Vegas  to lead the Spokane,
Washington-based Bulldogs (31-2) to a 14th straight win.  Saint Mary’s fell to 27-6, and the Gaels probably will get
an at-large NCAA tournament bid.  Davidson pushed its winning streak to 17 games with a 74-55
win against the College of Charleston last night in the Southern
Conference championship in Asheville,  North Carolina . De’Mon
Brooks had 24 points and eight rebounds to help the Wildcats
(26-7) defend their title.  JMU Wins  James Madison ended a 19-year NCAA tournament drought by
beating Northeastern 70-57 in the Colonial Athletic Association
final in Richmond, Virginia. The Dukes (20-14) used an early 23-
1 scoring run to open a 26-6 lead, with Rayshawn Goins scoring
13 of his 14 points during the first half.  Western Kentucky (20-15) won the Sun Belt Conference
championship for the second year in a row by beating Florida
International 65-63 in Hot Springs,  Arkansas .  Iona (20-13) defeated Manhattan 60-57 in a matchup of New
York rivals at the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference final in
Springfield,  Massachusetts .  Three more schools will earn automatic bids today as
Valparaiso faces Wright State in the Horizon League title game,
Long Island University Brooklyn meets Mount St. Mary’s for the
Northeast Conference championship, and South Dakota State plays
North Dakota State in the Summit Tournament final.  Harvard University , Liberty, Belmont, Florida Gulf Coast
and Creighton previously earned NCAA spots.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in  New York  at 
